column20: Thank you for choosing to participate in this study. Please read the consent form belowPurpose:This survey investigates people’s perception of social relationships.Procedure:You are invited to compete a questionnaire consisting of about 100 questions and some demographic information questions.Risks and Side Effects:There is no risk or side effect.Benefits:By completing this questionnaire, you will receive a monetary reward.Confidentiality:The results of this study may be published in an academic journal/book or used for teaching purposes, relevant scientific data may be shared to other researchers for further analysis. However, your name or other identifiers will not be used in any publication or teaching materials without your specific permission.Do you consent to participate in this study?
column21: In this survey you will be asked to rate relationships based on different bipolar scales. The entire survey should take about 15 minutes.At the top of each page, there will be two phrases on opposite ends of the presented slider bars. Please move the slider toward the phrase you feel best relates to the presented relationships. Sliders automatically start at one side of the bar and need to be moved, if only slightly, to register a response.?You will be presented with relationships throughout the survey, but the bipolar scales will change on each page. Please take into account all aspects of the relationships, including the way the two individuals in each relationship typically think and feel about each other, how they act and react toward each other, how they talk and listen to each other, and any other characteristics of the relationships that occur to you. It is important to consider the relationship as a whole and not just of one party's perspective.?Please answer each question carefully in order to have your assignment approved. There will be questions to test that you are taking the assignment seriously. If it is clear that you did not take this assignment seriously, it will not be approved and you will not receive payment for this assignment.

column74: "Activeness" EvaluationDefinition: A relationship is ‘Active’ if both people (a) are involved in a shared activity or event that grants the relationship, and (b) have direct and unequivocal interactions. Otherwise, the relationship is ‘Passive’.
